Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_narrow_channel(25.10)                      report_narrow_channel(25.10)

Name
       report_narrow_channel - Creates a report that contains a list of narrow
       channels

Syntax
       report_narrow_channel

       [-help]

       {-width <width>}

       [-ignore_placement_blockage ]

       [-no_merge_channel_check ]

       [-direction {x y xy}]

       [-active_objects  {macro  macroHalo  ioPad  ioCell  core fence hardBlkg
       softBlkg partialBlkg routeBlkg row}] }

       Creates a report that contains a list of narrow channels.

       Note: The report_narrow_channel command returns channel  boxes  as  its
       return value.

Parameters
       -active_objects {macro macroHalo ioPad ioCell core fence hardBlkg soft-
       Blkg partialBlkg routeBlkg row}
              Specifies the active objects for narrow channel checking.

              Default: "core macro macroHalo hardBlkg"

              Data_type: enum_list, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each report_narrow_channel parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man report_narrow_channel

       -direction {x y xy}
              Specifies the direction for checking narrow  channels.  You  can
              specify x, y, or xy.

              Default: xy

              Example:

              report_narrow_channel -width 100 -direction x

              report_narrow_channel -width 100 -direction y

              report_narrow_channel -width 100 -direction xy

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -ignore_placement_blockage
              When  specified,  the placement blockages are ignored while com-
              puting channel widths.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -no_merge_channel_check
              Specifies that the narrow channel error  boxes  will  be  merged
              into contiguous error boxes.

              Example:   report_narrow_channel   -width   100   -direction  xy
              -no_merge_channel_check

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -width <width>
              Specifies the width for checking the channels.

              Maximum: 100000

              Minimum: 0

              Data_type: float, optional

Example
       The following command checks for channels with width  1.0  and  ignores
       placement blockages:

       report_narrow_channel -width 1.0 -ignore_placement_blockage

